4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under current law, emergency medical transport
6 providers pay a quarterly assessment to provide
7 additional Medicaid enhancement payments for
8 maintenance and expansion of emergency medical
9 transport services. The assessment expires at the end
10 of the fiscal quarter starting July 1, 2028.
11 This bill would remove the sunset clause and
12 make the quarterly assessment permanent.
13
14
15 A BILL
16 TO BE ENTITLED
17 AN ACT
18
19 Relating to emergency medical transport providers; to
20 amend Sections 40-26B-91, 40-26B-94, and 40-26B-95, Code of
21 Alabama 1975, as last amended by Act 2025-370, 2025 Regular
22 Session; to make the assessment on emergency medical providers
23 permanent.
24 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
25 Section 1. Sections 40-26B-91, 40-26B-94, and
26 40-26B-95, Code of Alabama 1975, as last amended by Act
27 2025-370, 2025 Regular Session, are amended as follows:
28 "§40-26B-91
Page 1

"§40-26B-91
HB231 INTRODUCED
29 To provide further for the availability of indigent
30 health care, the operation of the Medicaid Program, and the
31 maintenance and expansion of emergency medical transport
32 services:
33 (1) Commencing no later than the fiscal quarter
34 starting April 1, 2023, and through and including the fiscal
35 quarter starting July 1, 2028, an assessment is imposed on
36 each emergency medical transport provider based on the number
37 of emergency medical transports. The quarterly assessment for
38 each emergency medical transport provider shall be calculated
39 based on the product of the assessment rate and the total
40 revenue received from emergency medical transports rendered by
41 the emergency medical transport provider from the previous
42 fiscal quarter.
43 (2) In consultation with the Alabama Medicaid Agency,
44 the department shall set an assessment rate each fiscal
45 quarter. The assessment rate shall be a maximum of 5.3
46 percent, subject to Section 40-26B-98(b). In consultation with
47 the Alabama Medicaid Agency, the department may change the
48 assessment rate each quarter to reduce the amount of surplus
49 assessments. Any surplus assessment from a previous quarter
50 may be used to reduce the assessment rate.
51 (3) The assessment imposed by this article is in
52 addition to all other taxes and assessments of any kind now
53 imposed by law."
54 "§40-26B-94
55 (a) Commencing no later than the fiscal quarter
56 starting April 1, 2023, and through and including the fiscal
