57 quarter starting July 1, 2028, on or before the 15th day after
58 the close of each fiscal quarter, every emergency medical
59 transport provider shall file with the department a statement
60 under penalty of perjury on forms prescribed by the
61 department, showing the total number of emergency medical
62 transports, the total amount of gross receipts for the subject
63 fiscal quarter, and other reasonable and necessary information
64 as the department, after consultation with the Alabama
65 Medicaid Agency and adoption of appropriate rules, may require
66 for the proper enforcement of this article.
67 (b) It shall be the duty of each emergency medical
68 transport provider to keep and preserve suitable books and
69 records as may be necessary to determine the amount of
70 assessments for which it is liable under this article. The
71 books and records shall be kept and preserved for a period of
72 not less than three years, and all such books and records
73 shall be open for examination during business hours by the
74 department or its duly authorized agents.
75 (c) All information secured pursuant to this article by
76 the department shall be confidential, as prescribed by Section
77 40-2A-10, except that the department may provide such
78 information to the Alabama Medicaid Agency as necessary for
79 the proper administration of the Medicaid Program, or for the
80 department's proper administration of the assessment levied by
81 this article.
82 (d) The department from time to time, as it deems
83 desirable, shall adopt reasonable rules as necessary to
84 provide for the orderly and efficient administration of the
