86 "§40-26B-95
87 (a) Commencing no later than the fiscal quarter
88 starting April 1, 2023, and through and including the fiscal
89 quarter starting July 1, 2028, the Alabama Medicaid Agency
90 shall pay an emergency medical transport enhancement each
91 fiscal quarter to emergency medical transport providers as set
92 forth in this section on or before the last day of the
93 quarter, except that Section 40-26B-97 shall apply to any
94 fiscal quarter for which federal approval has not been
95 obtained as of the first day of the fiscal quarter. The
96 emergency medical transport enhancement shall be paid in
97 addition to any other amounts payable to emergency medical
98 transport providers with respect to those services and shall
99 not affect any other payments to emergency medical transport
100 providers.
101 (b) For each fiscal quarter, the emergency medical
102 transport enhancement to each emergency medical transport
103 provider shall be calculated as the total number of emergency
104 medical transports reimbursed by the Alabama Medicaid Agency
105 as the primary payor in accordance with Chapter 8 of the
106 Medicaid Provider Manual to the emergency medical transport
107 provider in the preceding fiscal quarter multiplied by the
108 transport enhancement rate. The total emergency medical
109 transport enhancement to all providers shall not be greater
110 than the assessment pool.
111 (c) For each fiscal quarter, the Alabama Medicaid
112 Agency shall establish the transport enhancement rate based on
